Residents and motorist have been cautioned to avoid low-lying and flooded areas. JOHANNESBURG - Emergency services say they'll be on high alert in hotspots across the province as wet weather conditions are expected to persist for the rest of the weekend.Residents and motorist have been cautioned to avoid low-lying and flooded areas.Seven people died earlier this month and a hundred more were displaced in flash floods.The body of a toddler was found near the Jukskei River earlier this week.Johannesburg Emergency Service s Robert Mulaudzi says: We call on motorists take precautionary measures when driving and to avoid flooded areas. Residents in low-lying areas are urged to monitor water levels. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)